CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 19, 1955, pg. 9, reads: "The Lady Wins - They week's winner of the award for being spotted in one of the many crowds in which Courier photographers and reporters are always present is awarded to the lady ringed on the far right in picture printed above. The pictures was taken at the Centre Avenue YWCA last Sunday after the tea and panel discussion held there by the Greater Pittsburgh Improvement Association.  These people were snapped as they left eh YWCA.  All the lady has to do to claim her $5 bill is to present herself at the Courier city desk and properly identify herself. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Men and women wearing coats, gathered outside Centre Avenue YWCA, with sign on building reading "This is a red feather service of your community chest"
